FBIS3-43694 "drafr009_e_94009" FBIS-AFR-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Restates Good Neighborliness Plan AB1201154194 Lagos Voice of Nigeria in English 1030 GMT 12 Jan 93 AB1201154194 Lagos Voice of Nigeria Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Nigerian Government has restated its commitment to a policy of good neighborliness with [break in reception]. Brigadier General Fred Chijuka, who stated this, said Nigeria was not an aggressor. The country only carried out a routine relocation of troops on its eastern border, a measure that was not designed to embarrass any of its neighbors. He said that if there was any misunderstanding between Nigeria and Cameroon, the issue was already being resolved at the diplomatic level. The troops' relocation, according to him, was normal and aimed at enhancing the safety of its citizens. The Nigerian foreign minister, Mr. Babagana Kingibe, visited Cameroon last week on the border issue after which both countries agreed on a joint patrol to stem the clashes.
